  1. Decision Trees and Random Forests To predict room occupancy using the decision tree classification algorithm.
  1. Load the room occupancy data and train a decision tree classifier. Evaluate the predictive performance by reporting the accuracy obtained on the testing dataset.

## tree(formula = Occupancy ~ ., data = train)

  1. Train a random forests classifier, and evaluate the predictive performance by reporting the accuracy obtained on the testing dataset.

The accuracy of the model is 75.67%, which is relatively high.

As the number of trees grow, the error rate drops. We are unable of improving error after about 380 trees. Now lets tune mtry:

library(MASS)
train <- RoomOccupancy_Training
tuned <- tuneRF(train[,-6], train[,6], stepFactor = 0.9, plot = TRUE, ntreeTry = 350, trace = TRUE, improve = 0.05)
## mtry = 2  OOB error = 1.05% 
## Searching left ...
## mtry = 3     OOB error = 1.2% 
## -0.1428571 0.05 
## Searching right ...
## mtry = 1     OOB error = 1.2% 
## -0.1428571 0.05

Between 2 and 3 of mtry, the oob error decreases. So the best mtry would be 2.
